description: Confirms a job worker has received the specified job. Used for partner actions only.

parameters.name: jobId
parameters.description: The unique system-generated ID of the job.

parameters.name: nonce
parameters.description: A system-generated random number that CodePipeline uses to ensure that the job is being worked on by only one job worker. Get this number from the response to a  GetThirdPartyJobDetails request.

parameters.name: clientToken
parameters.description: The clientToken portion of the clientId and clientToken pair used to verify that the calling entity is allowed access to the job and its details.

nested_items.name: status
nested_items.description: The status information for the third party job, if any.
